Day 2 - Prompt Engineering

What I Learned:-

Today I learned about Prompt Engineering and how important it is when using AI tools like Claude.
Prompt Engineering means giving clear and detailed instructions so that AI can understand the task properly and provide better results.

Activity:-

First, I used a simple prompt:

Create an image explaining Prompt Engineering.

Observation:

The result was basic and did not contain much detail.
The output was simple but lacked clear explanations.

Then I used a more detailed prompt with proper instructions and context.

Observation:

The result was much better.
The explanation was clearer, more detailed, and easier to understand.
The output looked more professional and useful.

Example:-

Weak Prompt:
Make a website.

Improved Prompt:
Act as a senior frontend developer and create a responsive portfolio website using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
Include a hero section, projects section, contact form, and modern design.

Key Takeaways:-

- Clear prompts produce better results.
- Context helps AI understand the task.
- Detailed instructions improve output quality.
- Better prompts save time and effort.

Conclusion:-
  This activity helped me understand that the quality of the response depends on the quality of the prompt. Even small improvements in a prompt can make a big difference in the final output.
